accinations in Europe providing quite encouraging predictive\nperformance, based on the produced NRMSE values. Special emphasis is placed on\nproving the non-negativity of SEIHCRDV model, achieving a representative basic\nreproductive number R0 and demonstrating the existence and stability of disease\nequilibria according to the formula produced to estimate R0. The model\noutperforms in predictive ability not only deterministic approaches but also\nstate-of-the-art stochastic models that employ Kalman filters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 3 Jul 2022 07:47:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 16:01:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2022 08:15:51 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2022 07:53:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-30"}
